                        <h5 class="head-font"><strong>What are Cookies?</strong></h5>
                        <p>Cookies refer to small data files that are placed on your computer or mobile device when you visit a website. These files are commonly used by website owners to facilitate the proper functioning of their websites and enhance the reporting capabilities of their sites.</p>
                        <p>First-party cookies are those that are set by the website owner (in this case, RideCentric), whereas third-party cookies are those set by external parties other than the website owner. Third-party cookies may enable external features or functionalities on or through the website, such as advertising, interactive content, or analytics. Parties that set these third-party cookies can identify your computer when it accesses the website or other associated websites.</p>
                        <h5 class="head-font"><strong>Why do we use cookies?</strong></h5>
                        <p>We use both first-party and third-party cookies for a variety of reasons. Some cookies are deemed necessary for the technical operation of our Website, and we classify them as "essential" or "strictly necessary" cookies. Other cookies allow us to track and target the interests of our users to improve their experience on our Online Properties. Third parties may serve cookies through our Website for advertising, analytics, and other purposes, which are explained in greater detail below.</p>
                        <h5 class="head-font"><strong>How can I control cookies?</strong></h5>
                        <p>You have the right to decide whether to accept or reject cookies. You can exercise your cookie preferences through the Cookie Consent Manager, which permits you to select the categories of cookies that you accept or reject. Essential cookies cannot be rejected since they are necessary to provide you with our services.</p>
                        <p>The Cookie Consent Manager is located in the notification banner and on our website. If you choose to reject cookies, you may still access our website, but your ability to utilize certain functions and parts of our website may be limited. You may also modify your web browser settings to allow or block cookies.</p>
                        <p>The table below lists the particular types of first-party and third-party cookies that are served through our Website, as well as their respective purposes. Please note that the specific cookies used may vary depending on the specific Online Properties that you access.</p>
